# Stolution server cron rules — mirror of the Mac LaunchAgent
# Install: crontab -e (as user s903) and paste these lines
# Verify:  crontab -l | grep orchestrator
# Logs:    /home/s903/.cache/orchestrator/*.log
#
# ZERO Claude tokens. All pure-bash local scripts. The thin Claude scheduled
# tasks (thin-spawner, thin-alerter) are managed via Cowork's
# scheduled-tasks API, NOT cron — they need access to mcp__cowork__start_task
# and SendUserMessage.

# Every minute: poll session count, update state files, raise idle alarm if needed.
* * * * * /home/s903/caia/scripts/orchestrator/local-poller.sh && /home/s903/caia/scripts/orchestrator/idle-detector.sh

# Every hour: audit. Write anomaly marker if heartbeat shows stagnation.
7 * * * * /home/s903/caia/scripts/orchestrator/heartbeat-auditor.sh

# Daily 02:00: rotate poller log to keep disk usage bounded.
0 2 * * * gzip -k /home/s903/.cache/orchestrator/poller_log.tsv && mv /home/s903/.cache/orchestrator/poller_log.tsv.gz /home/s903/.cache/orchestrator/archive/poller_log_$(date +\%Y\%m\%d).tsv.gz && : > /home/s903/.cache/orchestrator/poller_log.tsv

# Every 10 min: drift check. If a recent spawned task is missing the sentinel
# block, log it.
*/10 * * * * /home/s903/caia/scripts/orchestrator/audit-spawn-prefix.sh

# Every 30 min: if Ollama is up, run the semantic-classifier on any
# pre-send-classifier "ambiguous" exits captured in the log. Pure local LLM,
# zero Claude tokens.
*/30 * * * * /home/s903/caia/scripts/orchestrator/ollama-semantic-classifier.sh
